Issues.Body:
Means that calling things like
`if (OleDragDropHandler.FreezePainting)` throws `NotImplementedException`

See https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/pull/2398
```cs
        [WinFormsFact]
        public void ControlDesigner_WndProc_InvokePaint_Success()
        {
            var designer = new SubControlDesigner();
            var m = new Message
            {
                Msg = (int)User32.WindowMessage.WM_PAINT
            };
            designer.WndProc(ref m);
        }

        private class SubControlDesigner : ControlDesigner
        {
            public new void WndProc(ref Message m) => base.WndProc(ref m);
        }
```

This test is expected to pass but throws `NotImplementedException` in .NET Core
